  "acceptance_criteria": [
    "Default player map uses topology-backed district polygons and explicit route polylines from read models; it must not synthesize player-facing territory from rectangular grid coordinates, hex axial/cube coordinates, sequential ids, or a hidden regular lattice.",
    "Polygon hit-test, district list, task rail, and inspector focus select the same active object and show consistent route/path preview reason codes.",
    "Player-facing route overlays come from topology edge sequence and route-node polyline data, not from polygon centroid adjacency, bounding boxes, nearest-neighbor geometry, or renderer-only connection guesses.",
    "Default overlays show only current decision-relevant routes; full route/pressure/debug overlays are opt-in and clearly labeled.",
    "Route preview shows edge sequence, mode, estimated days, bottleneck capacity, seasonal variation, known/unknown/blocked reasons, and result feedback in localized text.",
    "UI does not mutate WorldState directly; all state changes still go through existing GameCommand/preview/submit boundaries."
  ],
  "required_tests": [
    "git status --short",
    "node .agents/skills/monsoon-studio-orchestrator/scripts/taskctl.mjs validate M7-MAP-TOPOLOGY-CLIENT-001",
    "git diff --check",
    "pnpm --filter @monsoon/map-renderer test",
    "pnpm --filter web test",
    "pnpm build:web",
    "pnpm storybook:build",
    "pnpm test:e2e",
    "pnpm check",
    "Playwright screenshots at 1440x900 and 1280x720 proving default map no longer reads as a rectangular board or regular hex/lattice board",
    "Playwright or component tests proving visual-neighbor-without-route and visually-distant-explicit-route cases display the correct reason codes"
  ],
